POST /v1/transactions/{businessTransactionId}/override
GET /v1/transactions/{businessTransactionId}/override

Locked design notes
overrideId uniquely identifies the override artifact.
overriddenBy and overriddenAt are generated by Parmana and are not supplied by the client.
The original policy decision is not duplicated in this response; it remains part of the Business Transaction and Execution Trust Record.
The response represents only the newly created or retrieved Override resource, keeping it consistent with the resource-oriented API design you've locked.


